    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "Inverted ACL authorization logic in aclsAllowAccess: the condition '(denyAclExists(acls) && allowAclExists(acls))' allows access when BOTH deny and allow rules exist, which is backwards. Correct logic should allow access only when NO deny rule exists AND allow rule exists. This causes authorization bypass where protected resources become accessible.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/core/src/main/scala/kafka/security/authorizer/AclAuthorizer.scala
